      "comment": "LIMBERING (6) has speed to burn and was a determined winner in this grade earlier in the prep. Will push forward again from the draw and will prove tough to reel in if left alone. IN YOUR WORDS (4) ultimately left herself too much ground to bridge last start as favourite but did finish with full of running. If they can settle a pair or two closer this time, she will take some stopping. BLUE ISLES (3) returns over what looks short of a preferred trip but should get a soft run from the low draw for Milnes and did shed her maiden over this journey. Don't take her lightly. GRINZINGER GOLD (1) got off the mark in style last time at Port Lincoln when leading pillar-to-post. Should come on from that but isn't drawn as kindly this time and loses Milnes.",
